  "text": "We then addressed the question of which biochemical pathway is responsible for At-TSPO degradation in eukaryotic cells. There are two major proteolytic systems for degradation in eukaryotes: the proteasome pathway for short-lived proteins and the lysosomal or vacuolar system of degradation by autophagy for longlived proteins, such as At-TSPO [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
